<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-246-025 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 772 211</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Jan 8 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New for Macintosh: Ethernet cards from Apple.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Rosenbaum, Daniel J.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (Product development).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Topic:     Product DevelopmentCommunications Boards/CardsEthernetCablesConnectivity.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW FOR MACINTOSH: Ethernet Cards from Apple 01/08/91 CUPERTINO, CALIFORNIA,U.S.A.andP;  1991 JAN 8 (NB) -- Apple Computer has announced a new line of circuitcards that let most expandable Macintoshes be hooked directly into high-speedEthernet networks.andM;The new cards include models for the newly shipping Macintosh LC and anotherthat will fit all models in the Macintosh II series.andP;  Apple said thirdparties will be making cards for other Macintoshes, including the Classic.andM;Prices and availability for the new products were not announced.andM;Also announced were three media adapters, which allow the cards to use thefour types of Ethernet cabling: fiber optic, thick coaxial, thin coaxial, andtwisted pair.andP;  All products, Apple said, comply with the IEEE 802.3 standard,which covers Ethernet.andP;  The thin coax connector complies with the 10Base2standard, the company said, and the twisted pair adapter complies with the10BaseT standard.andM;The new products appear to replace the Apple EtherTalk NB Card, whichdirectly supported only thin coax connections.andP;  Other media could beconnected only through external transceivers.andM;Apple's Ethernet products expand the Macintosh's networking options.andP;  Alreadyavailable are connectivity products for SNA and Token-Ring environments.andM;Thenew Apple networking products were simultaneously launched in the UK.andM;&quot;These products mark an important milestone for Apple's networkingtechnology,&quot; said Steve Everhard, Apple UK's networking and communicationsmarketing manager.andP;  &quot;We have simplified the use of Ethernet and increasednetwork reliability.andP;  We are also offering new affordable options and, as aresult, Apple has become the first vendor to make the value of Ethernetreadily available to mainstream users.&quot;andM;The new products include a UKP 112 Ethernet LC card for the Mac LC series,along with a Nubus (NB) card for the Nubus-based Macs at UKP 227.andP;  The LCcard is available immediately in the UK, while the NB card ships beginning inMay.andM;The UK announcement included the Ethernet cabling system which includes threemedia adapters - all priced at UKP 98 - to connect the cards to anyindustry-standard Ethernet media.andM;(Daniel J. Rosenbaum/Steve Gold/19910107/Press Contact: Brooke Cohan, AppleComputer, 408 974-3019; Apple UK - Tel: 081-862-3928)</TEXT></DOC>